''AKA Minimal Evaluation, McCarthy Evaluation''

[[Short-circuit Evaluation]] is a [[Compiler Optimization]] whereby the second argument of a boolean operation is evaluated only if the first argument does not suffice to determine the value of the expression.

```lua
> = true and print('hi')
hi
nil
> = false and print('hi')
false
```

